  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strenghthening Lobby and Advocacy skills for Kuapa Kokoo Farmers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Implement FACT trajectory.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kuapa Kooko Farmers Union (KKFU) is made up of 87.968 members divided into 57 Primary cooperative Societies which are spread in 6 out of the 7 cocoa districts in Ghana. It is arguably the biggest agricultural cooperatives in Ghana. The BHAG of the union and its objective for working with Agriterra is to strengthen at least 10 of its primary cooperatives and make them financially sustainable within the next four years. To use their strength in numbers to influence government policy to the benefit of its members   Agriterra support to Kuapa Kokoo in 2019 was to implement the Farmers Advocacy Consultation Tool (FACT) to address the issue of limited extension delivery which was identified as a major hindrance to the activities of KKFU members which ultimately resulted in the low production of the cooperative. The major source of income for the union is the premium gained from selling certified cocoa beans. However  productivity is a big challenge since the estimated output is far more than the actual realised production. This could stem from two major issues  limited member commitment which could result inside selling and low productivity per acre as a result of limited access to inputs. As such  the union wants to implement an input scheme at the society level and to make them financially sustainable while making inputs easily accessible to its members. Ever since its existence  the union has not done any study to know the actual status in strength or weaknesses of its member cooperatives. To know which societies can better implement the scheme  there is a need for a categorisation exercise which will help identify the state and areas of improvement for all the 57 cooperatives. Also  as a continuation of the FACT trajectory started with Kuapa Kooko in 2019  some more activities will be taken to complete the entire cycle of the FACT. This FACT trajectory will result in influencing government policy towards investing in  ICT in extension delivery which will result indirectly in increased production for the union. Currently  Women form less than 5% of the leadership at the primary society level though out of the total membership  26.3909 (30%) are women. Therefore as part of strengthening the PCs  attention will be given to female leadership to enable women participation in the decision making of the envisaged strengthened cooperatives.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project consists of a trajectory to complete the full cycle of FACT in order to strengthen the lobby and advocacy skills of the Kuapa Kokoo Co-operative union farmers. This will enable them to lobby government to contribute to relevant national policies to the benefit of their members and also for the primary societies to lobby at the union level. The ultimate outcome will feed into the FAO-FFF Phase II in Ghana with which Agriterra is collaborating in terms of support to Kuapa Kokoo..Key activities will be a preparatory workshop  member consultation  participatory research  validation and write workshop for action and follow-up workshop.</narrative>
  </description>
